GM Notes: Running The Three Fires
Unchosen Consequences Delivery
The adventures the party does NOT choose will escalate off-screen. Deliver consequences gradually:
Session After the Choice:
Rumors and refugee reports about the ignored crises.
NPCs react to the party's choice with approval or criticism.
Two Sessions Later:
Direct consequences hit:
Riften Ignored: General Caelinus falls ill with the plague. Davinia receives urgent summons to Solitude.
Darkwater Ignored: Eastmarch forests attack travelers. Spriggans become hostile everywhere.
Dawnstar Ignored: Vokun's draugr army marches south toward Windhelm.
Long-Term:
The ignored crises become major plot points in Act IV.
The Dragon Cult Clock advances based on which adventure was ignored.
Pacing Recommendations
Each adventure should take 6-8 hours (2 sessions).
Session 1: Prologue + Sections 1-2 (Setup & Investigation/Infiltration)
 Session 2: Sections 3-5 (Climax & Resolution)
Character Arc Integration
Use these adventures to advance personal arcs:
Alfonso: Riften directly challenges his genius and introduces the Alchemical Arms Race.
Saijah: Darkwater forces her Tier 3 Crossroads (Mercy vs. Efficiency).
Davinia: Dawnstar tests her leadership and relationship with Galmar.
Orion: All three adventures involve navigating his dual loyalties (Brotherhood vs. Valerius vs. Party).
Kyboh: His gloves continue to deteriorate across all adventures, creating urgency to reach Hjolmar's forge.
The Weight of Choice
The core theme of this module is triage. The party cannot save everyone. They can only choose which fire to put out, and they must live with the consequences of the others burning.
Use this to create meaningful stakes. Every choice matters. Every consequence lands.


